	   <tr><td colspan=2>Good question. The druid epic, the <a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=3571 target=_new>Nature Walkers Scimitar</a> is 1HS so you will want to work on your 1HS.&nbsp;&nbsp;That said, in game there are about two to three times as many 1HB items available for druids to use as there are 1HS items, and this tends to be reflected in the lower price and ease of finding these items in the bazaar, also making them a viable choice.  As to 2HB, the delay tends to be much higher on these weapons, making it harder to train and maintain you weapon skill in these weapons.  I also dislike 2HB weapons as they take up both melee slots, and I don't think there is a single 2HB weapon that has better stats than a 1HS + secondary item attainable at the same level.<br><br>After level 20 you will find that you are no longer meleeing MOBs to any great extent and so you weapon skills advances slow right down, and by the time you hit 34 and you start quading, you almost never hit a MOB.  Because of this try and max out your weapon skills while you are still low as the mobs hit less hard and at later levels you spend most of your time medding during battles(I don't think I've seen a weapon increase for a few levels now).<br><br>If you want to keep you weapon skills up, it helps if you have low delay weapons as this allows you more chances of hits per fight, and thus more chances for a weapon skill increase.  Good (cheap) weapons are things like the <a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=3 target=_new>Kerran Fishing Pole</a> or the <a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=467 target=_new>Abandoned Orc Shovel</a>, both having one of the lowest delays for their weapon types, and both are free.<br><br>A good way to work on your weapon skills is fear kiting, although this becomes more dangerous the higher you get because the gulf between what hit points you have compared to what damage a mob can inflict on you widens.  You can also try meleeing when a snared mob turns and trys to escape when it's hps get below 10%, as they don't hit back when they are running away.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Dec 11 10:49:58 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
