	   <a name=103935302795965></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103935302795965><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=103935302795965>RE: fishing</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=103935302795965#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=87819><span id=Sage>iteck</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>124 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Dec 8th 8:34 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>To fish you need:<br><b>1:</b> One of your skill buttons set-up with the fishing skill.<br><b>2:</b> A fishing pole of some sort equipped in your primary weapon slot.<br><b>3:</b> Bait of some sort (you don't need to put the bait in any particular slot and it can be hidden in one of your bags if you want).<br><b>4:</b> Water.<br><br>Once you have got all the above worked out, go to the waters edge and press your fishing skill button.&nbsp;&nbsp;You should then get one off the following messages:<br><i>You think you are heading ______.</i> Make sure you have set up you skill button correctly.<br><i>You need to put your fishing pole in your primary hand.</i> Check step 2 above.<br><i>You can't fish without fishing bait, go buy some.</i> Check step 3 above.<br><i>You cast your line.</i> Congratz you have started fishing.<br><br>After a couple of seconds you should then get one off the following messages:<br><i>Trying to catch land sharks perhaps?</i> Check step 4 above.  This can happen if you are too far from the water edge.  Sometimes you can be what looks like miles away from the water but the game still allows you to fish, other times you can be so close to the edge that your feet are getting wet, but still the game gives you this message.  Just move a bit closer and try again.  If you get a <i>You must be on dry land to fish.</i> then you know you got too close.<br><i>You didn't catch anything.</i> Bad luck, try again.<br><i>You caught ____ ____!</i> You caught whatever the message told you.<br><i>You caught, something…</i> You have normally caught a Fish Scale, a rusty dagger or a tattered cloth sandal, but sometimes, depending on the zone it can be items like saltwater seaweed which can have some limited value or use.<br><b>Note:</b> I don't know if it's skill based or it was a recent change in-game, but I'm sure I get more messages telling me what rubbish I have caught rather than the you caught something… message now then when I was low level at fishing.<br><br>You can also get the following messages:<br><i>You can't fish while holding something.</i> You need to have a empty cursor.<br><i>You lost your bait.</i> Bad luck.  You also use up one bait whenever you catch something (I'm sure this relatively recent and you only used to use up a bait if you caught a fish).<br><i>You stop fishing and go on your way.</i> You moved before you finished fishing.  Can happen if you are standing too close to a wall/low ceiling.<br><i>You spill your beer while bringing in your line.</i> Go figure!<br><br>In the addition if you have a tackle box you can craft some items.  A good site for information on this is EqTraders: <a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/secrets/recipes_fishing.htm" target=_new>http://www.eqtraders.com/secrets/recipes_fishing.htm</a><br>This part of the skill had always been overlooked by Verant, and was very basic, but with the (fairly) recent up-grade to the trade skills, it is beginning to be fleshed out.<br><br>On the whole, fishing is just one big time-sink, but if you are sitting on your butt by some water medding and guild chat has gone quite then you might as well pull out you fishing pole and see what you can catch.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
