<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=103917058780947></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103917058780947><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=103917058780947>RE: Good Solo Class?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=103917058780947#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=87819><span id=Sage>iteck</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>124 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Dec 6th 5:53 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yes, druids in my view, are still the (2nd) best solo class in the game.<br><br>From a purely solo point of view:<br><b>Transport:</b> Yes bards get Selo's which allow them to run faster than sow, and wizards get more ports then druids, but druids get both.&nbsp;&nbsp;The ability to get to anywhere with only a few zones and outrun most mobs really helps druids to solo.<br><br><b>Healing:</b> Although it is possible for classes without heal to solo, with the ability to heal yourself you can massively reduce down time.  Not only do druids get the cleric series of heal spells (be it at a later level), druids also get their own regain over time series of spells.  Druids also get spells that allow them to cure disease and poisons.<br><br><b>Mob control:</b> Although nowhere close to the enchanter, druids still get an impressive range of spells to enable them to control mobs.  The ability to slow the mobs speed (ensnare line of spells) and to stop the mob from moving all together, play an important port of almost all druid soloing tactics, and can allow the druid to solo mobs, or groups of mobs, without ever being hit by the mob(s).  Druids also get Harmony at a very low level, which although recently nurfed, is a extremely powerful spell that allows camps to be broken with very little danger to the druid.  Also, although restricted to animals, druids get a spells that allow us to charm and fear animals, opening up additional possibilities to solo.<br><br><b>Damage:</b> Fact: Druids melee like weak girls (apologies to any weak girls out there, or any druids who were under any different illusions ).  That said, druids get some pretty impressive offensive spells.  Druid direct damage spells (DDs), although not as great as wizard DDs, are nothing to be sniffed at, druid damage over time spells (DOTs) are not quite as good as necro DOTs, but are still very good, and on top of that druids get area effect DDs, which allow druids to 'quad' kite (take on four targets at the same time).<br><br><b>Buffs:</b> Druids get forms of almost all the buffs available within the game.  These include speed (sow), levitate, water breathing, damage shields, armour class buffs, hitpoint buffs, attack buffs, two illusions (tree and wolf), strength buffs, resist buffs, and with the recent introduction of Spirit of Ash, a self mana regain spell at level 39.<br><br>Basically druids are extremely versatile, which makes them one of the strongest classes in the game.  Druids can solo in a variety of ways including quad kiteing, fear kiteing, root and rot, snare and blast and charm kiteing.  With their porting abilities druids can leave over-camped zones and move to less busy ones, and have the ability to 'hop' back to the bank to sell and unload at any time.<br><br>On top all the above, druids are also good in groups, and can fit into any number of roles.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
