	   <tr><td colspan=2>A comment on pointless thought #2. I hadn't played my lvl 40 druid for a while, and suddenly got the urge to start using the lvl 44 druid spells. So I bound myself near the Ulthork camp in EW, ported to the Nexus, and donated for KEI. I gated back to EW and started quad kiting ulthork hunters and warriors, and woolly rhinos (often all 3 types together). With KEI I always had enough mana, even if had to finish off a rhino with&nbsp;&nbsp;DoT or 2 while medding back from almost OOM. And of couse the KEI-accelerated medding back to full mana had me ready for another quad kite in a very short time.<br><br>When KEI wore off, I'd port back to the Nexus, donate for KEI again, and sell my loot in Shadowhaven. With the velium weapons and ulthork hides, I ALWAYS made more PP than the 100pp I donated for the KEI. Then back to EW for more fast XP. (BTW, this doesn't even count the 500-600pp I made from the Ulthork Tusk quest in the process)<br><br>In a very short time I reached 44, with plently of cash for my lvl 44 spells. <br><br>I've stopped buying KEI for now (which is hard, because its VERY easy to get addicted to), but will probably start the process again (in a new zone?) the next time I get the urge for some fast leveling.<br><br><br>Ayudante<br>44th season Wood Elf Druid<br>Zeb<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
