	   <tr><td colspan=2>I’ve been playing EQ since Oct. of 01 and I have a 45th level druid and a 47th level ranger.&nbsp;&nbsp;I also do a lot of quests and a lot of trade skills.  I’ve never been in much of a hurry to level my characters.  As long as I’ve been having fun I haven’t worried about it.  However, as most of my guild mates have been hitting the early fifties and working on AA points, I’ve been thinking more and more about leveling.  And since being higher level will also help with my trade skills, it couldn’t hurt to do a bit more of it.  As soon as I get a better graphics card I plan to move into Jaggedpine.  It’s a great zone for druids, especially, till at least the early fifties.  And I can gather items for my baking skill.  <br><br>But in the long run, Rofeus is right.  There’s not time limit to reaching 65th level or even a requirement to do so.  All we have to do is have fun.  So if being higher level will add to your fun, then go for it. If not then don’t worry about it.  <br><br>&nbsp;<br><b>Namir Shadowstalker</b><br>Wood Elf Ranger, 51st Season<br><b>Calabar Silverthorn</b><br>Wood Elf Druid, 51st Season<br><b>Pait</b><br>Vah Shir Shaman, 39th Season<br><br><b>Seventh Hammer</b></td></tr>
