	   <a name=103835254017291></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103835254017291><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=103835254017291>RE: epic quest?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=103835254017291#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=166643><span id=Scholar>tamarask</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>51 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Nov 26th 6:38 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.12]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>EQDruids.com has several very helpful guides to the Druid epic.&nbsp;&nbsp;As for whether or not it's difficult, the answer is yes. It's an epic weapon, remember. It's not supposed to be a walk in the park to get it. However, it's a lot of fun to do this quest. Some epic quests are more difficult than others. The druid epic is on the lower end of the difficulty scale. Most of the quest I was able to do solo (foraging, hand-ins, mammoth in Everfrost, Barracuda in LOIO, Gorilla in EJ, Hill giant in Rathe, etc). Several other parts you can do with just one group. The most difficult part of the whole thing for me was not Faydedar (wussy dragon my guild killed with just 9 peeps, two of the peeps 2-boxed). The Reavers were the most difficult for me. Not because they are super tough if you have tankage, but because of the rarity of that darn Jade Reaver. We spent around 5 hours and killed around 15 Reavers before one dropped. Venril Sathir Remains also takes a couple groups. Perhaps less if you have a group of experienced, 60+ players. VSR is also a random spawn time, dependent on the death of Venril Sathir, so you will need to basically bind yourself at KC and keep a close eye on the spawn. And Ulump is almost totally MR, so you need tankage for him. With the exception of the Jade Reaver, VSR, Ulump and Faydedar, I had all my epic kills completed within 3 weeks. Due to getting the peeps and the spawn of the other mobs, it took me a total of 6 months from start to finish. If I had worked harder on getting the raids together sooner, I could most likely have finished the epic in the space of a couple months. As VSR drops 2 stones (also needed for ranger epic, btw), you can generally get your guild or a pickup group if you're not guilded, to do that raid happily.<br><br>As for the best armor, I would go with Elyssian. No drop armor from Umbral Plains. Personally I'm currently wearing the Kael quest breastplate and a lot of SS armor. <br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
