	   <tr><td colspan=2>My advice to a true newbie....<br><br>1. Log off and get some sleep, EQ will be here tommorrow.<br><br>2. Always anticipate when the spouse or significant other is going to ask you to do something....always be near somewhere safe to camp at in a hurry.<br><br>3. Caffeine is your friend<br><br>4. Nicotine is your friend if your a smoker.&nbsp;&nbsp;If your not a smoker, try everclear....it makes inhaling the smoke seem a lot less painful in comparison.<br><br>5. Have your resume up to date...you are eventually going to seriously give some thought to finding a part-time job and putting your significant other to work full-time to support your new addiction.<br><br>6. That pretty female druid your hitting on?...SURE...Whatever you want to believe is fine by me...most EQ'ers obey the &quot;don't ask, don't tell policy&quot;.  You may not want to ask...cause they may tell.<br><br>7.  Start buying EQ for friends....you gonna want to talk about your experiences with real life people....and if they don't play, you might get institutionalized.<br><br>8.  Honestly?  Skip 1 through 7...cause it doesn't matter.  Your hooked...so have fun!!<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Geil Kellelottendi<br>Founder and Leader<br>Souls of Loyalty<br>Erollisi Marr</td></tr>
