	   <tr><td colspan=2>When I was fighting in The Overthere, I stayed there and Fought Sarnaks and Cockatrices and Tiger's/Tigresses till about lvl 38 (that, on top of Kiting Dorf's in BBM), and then I went and Started Grouping in DL. DL is Good Exp in Group, and Solo, if you can handle Soloing In DL, Cause you Really have to know where your Hunting. My Suggestion, If you going to Group, look for a group at the North East Ruins. If your Going to Solo Here's what I Did, and am Still Doing:<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;   When running out of the Ice Cavern, Follow the Zoneline that is to your Right. Follow it Till you Get out of the Snowy Area, and it Turns into Grass. When you get to this Area, Stop, and Turn to your Left. You'll See a Cliff that Hang's out over into the Ice. Stand at the End of this Cliff. This Is a Rather Safe Spot. Ive hunted here Many times with Friends and Rarely does something walk near and Aggro us. Anyways, When you look across the Ice Lake, There will be a Castle on the Other Side of it. Run over there, and there will be Giants, Drac's, Yeti's, and a Few other Things That Roam Around, but They are all usually Seperated Out far enough that you can keep from getting Add's. Usually you can Snare the Mob you want, and By the time you get back to the Ledge from Kiting it, you've usually Got it Close to Dead, and trying to run. Hope this Helps.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Nov 19 04:35:23 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Tluadan Mudvayne&nbsp;&nbsp; <br>&lt;Evil Dynasty&gt;<br>53rd Season Druid</td></tr>
