	   <tr><td colspan=2>I personally never utilized the overthere, so I can't comment on how long to stay there. However, when I was around your level I believe I was hunting in Everfrost.&nbsp;&nbsp;The mammoths are good experience and tusks can sell to vendors for up to 10pp (depending on charisma).  The tainted/corrupted mammoths also drop pieces for the druid epic quest. There is also a camp of icy orcs that is worth hunting if the mammoth hunting is slow.  Use harmony on the named orc (Redwind) and you can single pull the others. There are 5 total and the spawn time is just about perfect.  They also drop pp and fine steel weapons.  Then, after you get your AoE lightning spell head to Iceclad to quad cougars (no money, but occasional cougar claw earring and great exp.). Once cougars started turning light blue I headed to Eastern wastes to quad ulthorks and coldain and I'm still getting lots of experience at level 45.  Plus, coldain heads and ulthork tusks can be used in some nice quests.  <br><br>I don't know if this is the best advice...just they way I did things.  Good luck!<br><br>Iindarie<br>Druid wood elf of 45 seasons<br>Brell Serilis<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Nov 17 19:36:33 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
