	   <tr><td colspan=2>My Suggestions on how to gain xp fast:<br><br>1) Faydewer: Go to CB and find/start a group that chain pull's. On my bard, when I played him in CB, I helped with meleeing the orc's, and while me and one warrior was killing, the Paladin was pulling again, and the warrior pulling while the pally was killing. Was good quick xp, and wasent all that hard to do, as long as we didnt pull something that was way to hard, which you do come across that problem every so often. Also, go to BBM and Kill at the Chess Board. they should con white/Dark blue to ya by now. Other good place is the Court yard in Unrest (not to sure of what they would con at lvl 10. I didnt touch unrest till about lvl 18.<br><br>Antonica: Go to Black Burrow, and Do the same there as Suggested for CB. Its Harder to find a group in Black Burrow (on veeshan) because not as many people go to it as they do CB. Also, Good xp is to just find a warrior, Keep him healed, and let him kill the Crap out of some Wolf's, Bears, Lions, and Pincer beetles in NK. Only thing about NK is it has alot of High Lvl Named Mobs (ie, Grimfeather, Silver Griffon, That Goblin Dude who's name i dont remember.) and then on top of that, There are alot of just Regular Griffon Mob's of Diffrent levels that Druids are KOS to (Wood elf druids anyways). I would Also Suggest checking out Befallen. So many people Underestimate Befallen, But it is SUCH a great place for lvling at your lvl. I got my Bard from lvl 10 to 14 Pretty Quick there. Once again, its another place you'll have probs soloing in as a druid,Cause your KOS, so you'll need to find you a tank to group with and go with you.But it souldnt be hard to find a lvl 10 Warrior in WC/EC/Freeport area Because of Freeport and The Dark elf City (which your More likely to get a Shadow Knight out of, which are good tanks) being around there.<br><br>Odus: Get a Port to Antonica or Faydewer if you somehow managed to get into this pit. Im sorry, but Odus xp Sucks quite Badly, and i belive i speek for most all Classes when i say that.<br><br>As for Velious, Kunark and Luclin, I have no clue, because I never went to Kunark or Velious untill I was about lvl 20 or so when i went to Lake of Ill Omen, and I didnt get the Luclin expansion untill I was about lvl 23-25, which i was prob missing out on some good Low level Exp, but im not sure.<br><br>Hopefully this will help you.<br><br>Edited:<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;Correction on the last paragraph. When i said &quot;I didnt get the Luclin expansion Till i was about lvl 23-25&quot; It Gave some the Impression that I never fought in Luclin. I did Fight in Pauldal Cavern's from somewhere around in them level's to 27 or 28. I was not there for a Lengthy Amount of time, but the little time i was there was good xp. Sorry about that.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Nov 20 04:07:13 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Tluadan Mudvayne&nbsp;&nbsp; <br>&lt;Evil Dynasty&gt;<br>53rd Season Druid</td></tr>
