	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.55]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>A good spot for experience at your level, and perhaps the very best spots in the game, is Paludal Caverns on Luclin.&nbsp;&nbsp;The zone is located directly off the friendly zone of Shadow Haven.  Many of the once popular leveling areas are now all but deserted because these people can now be found in Paludal.  So not surprisingly the zone can be crowded.  But that also makes it easier to find a group.  And with the new Planes of Power you can reach the zone easily from any starting city in Norrath.  I’ve read posts and spoken with dozens of people who have leveled here faster than anyplace they have ever hunted.  The zone is good from about 12 to 23.  You can start earlier and push it a bit longer, but that seems to be about the average range.  The zone gives a large experience bonus, which is why leveling goes so quickly.<br><br>Best of luck,<br><br>&nbsp;<br><b>Namir Shadowstalker</b><br>Wood Elf Ranger, 51st Season<br><b>Calabar Silverthorn</b><br>Wood Elf Druid, 51st Season<br><b>Pait</b><br>Vah Shir Shaman, 39th Season<br><br><b>Seventh Hammer</b></td></tr>
