	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, I understand where the original poster is coming from.&nbsp;&nbsp;A friend had EQ, and I started as an Iksar Necro in Kunark.  What a tough starting choice.  No easy supply of porters, lack of people doing trade-skills, and no easy source of income.  Struggled to get him up to lvl 34 (toughest part was getting those spells that were combined using a skill...)<br><br>Then, I started a druid and have not looked back!  I was a human druid, and making coins hand-over-fist.  Yes, I exploited a few bears for their HQ pelts, but found lots of ppl to sell these type of things to.  After I started porting folks, some more coins came in.  What I thought was innovative was the introduction of the Bazaar, focus items and KEI...  I have found that things seem to progress MUCH faster.  Yes, there have not been glorified changes to DD/DoT/etc for spellcasting, but any dramatic changes would probably get complaints from other classes.  Remember, after Luclin came out, it was still some time before the Bazaar functionality came out.  Hopefully, PoP will have something waiting in the wings...<br>&nbsp;<br>Drack - Solusek Ro<br>35th Scale Necromancer (Retired)<br>Denaar<br>52nd Level Druid (new Main...)</td></tr>
