	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have a lvl 40 Druid, and Alot of the times when im soloing, i use My Charm Spell Alot in certain places or when Grouping with other caster friends that cant Tank, and letting the Pet Tank. The Way I always do it is I Snare the animal, and then Charm it. the Reason for this is so if the charm hits it, and fails, the Animal dont Run at me and start attacking (snare usually Grabs first time for me, so its safer this way). The Other Reason for this is because when the Charm Breaks, I can Run From it and Re-snare and Charm it again with little problems. Snaring the Animal While its charmed Will not break the Charm, But Charm ill Resist more than Ensnare (for me anyways). Root on the Other hand, Do NOT use, because Root Does have a DD Effect to it, and when you DD the Animal, it does Break Charm. I Personally Have never Rooted my pet, but thinking Logically, it would break it since a DD would.Anyways, Hope this helps.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Nov 13 04:27:56 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Tluadan Mudvayne&nbsp;&nbsp; <br>&lt;Evil Dynasty&gt;<br>53rd Season Druid</td></tr>
